00 The Global Times launched its iPad app on Jan 31, 2022, the Chinese New Year's Eve, hoping to offer our readers around the globe access to exclusive stories, investigative reports and multi-media products in one portal, with high definition e-newspaper available at readers' fingertips.Readers will be able to get the latest headlines about Chinese society and economy from the new app’s homepage while staying informed about the most recent happenings with our real-time notifications. From breaking news to opinion, business, life and sports, 12 built-in channels give you our expert coverage, commentary and analysis.The app will also let you tap into GT’s special coverage on topics such as COVID-19 and the Winter Olympics with original reporting from our journalists.  You can also absorb facts and read news in a more innovative way with our infographics, data visualization products and videos. “Z-talk” and “I-talk” are GT’s new programs where our anchors talk with big names from different fields. GT’s cartoons combine aesthetics with journalism. Using sarcasm and parody, they offer a fresh way to understand geopolitics. Scan the QR code and download the app now!